## Data conventions

### `VISA_DETAILS` structure

Country-specific researched data lives in the `VISA_DETAILS` object keyed by `[countryCode][visaId]`. Default guidance for each visa type lives in `VISA_DETAILS_DEFAULTS`. The `getVisaDetails()` lookup prefers country-specific; falls back to defaults.

**Countries with researched entries (as of April 2026):** DE, PT, ES, NL, IE, MT, FR, IT, GR, CZ, EE (11 of 27).

**Fallback countries (show "General guidance" amber chip):** AT, BE, BG, HR, CY, DK, FI, HU, LV, LT, LU, PL, RO, SK, SI, SE (16 of 27).

When a user requests new country data, research via web search of official portals + at least one secondary source (Fragomen, Jobbatical, CitizenRemote, etc.). Never fabricate specific thresholds — if data isn't found, use the default.

### Data freshness

All figures labeled "as of early 2026" with explicit "verify at official portal" disclaimers. Immigration rules change quarterly. Expect a refresh pass at least annually, ideally triggered by a country's major reform (e.g., when Germany Blue Card thresholds reset each January).

### Czech Republic / Czechia naming

The country is labeled `"Czechia (Czech Republic)"` to match both the country's formal short-form preference and the name Americans recognize. Don't shorten to just "Czechia" — users searching for "Czech Republic" need the parenthetical match.

