## Accessibility commitments (508 / WCAG 2.1 AA)

A full 508 compliance pass was completed. The tool is AA-compliant. When editing, maintain these:

- **Contrast:** All text combos verified ≥ 4.5:1. Never use `#8A94AD` (2.82:1 on cream background — fails).
- **ARIA patterns:** Use `aria-pressed` toggles, not `role="radio"` (which requires arrow-key nav we don't implement). Use `role="group"` for toggle collections, not `role="radiogroup"`.
- **Hover-only info banned:** Every `title` tooltip must also have an `aria-label` with the same information. Don't introduce a tooltip without a screen-reader equivalent.
- **Heading hierarchy:** h1 (site) → h2 (page) → h3 (section) → h4 (subsection). Don't skip levels.
- **Flags in context:** When a country name is adjacent, the `<Flag>` component is decorative-by-default (no alt, `aria-hidden`). When a flag stands alone, pass an `alt` prop.
- **Overflow regions are keyboard-scrollable:** `tabIndex={0}` + `role="region"` + descriptive `aria-label` on every horizontally-scrolling container.
- **Live regions:** The floating comparison tray uses `aria-live="polite"` so state changes announce.
- **Sliders have `aria-valuetext`:** Descriptive ("3 of 5 — moderate"), not just numeric.

### Skip link

The skip link uses CSS `:focus` pseudo-class in a `<style>` block, not inline `onFocus`/`onBlur` handlers. Don't refactor it back to inline handlers.

### Language attribute

Set in `index.html` as `<html lang="en">`. It's not settable from inside the React component, so don't try.

